Rating: 4
This is a different, but tasty pate. Easy. Next time I would increase the thyme and brandy to help balance the blue cheese. Make sure to serve at room temperature so that the flavors come through. I froze leftovers in thick slices. You can thaw in the fridge with excellent results.

Rating: 2
Just ok. I am a huge pate fan and was really looking forward to this one. I used high quality imported blue, 12 year old McCallan instead of brandy and made sure to caramelize the onions but the result lacked depth and complexity of flavor I expected from all these great ingredients.

Rating: 4
This was awesome! I was short of brandy so subbed in some Marsala. The blue cheese doesn't jump out at you, rather it is a subtle back note, which just kind of lingers on the tongue. We served this on toasted garlic baugette slices and drank with a Zinfandel. Outstanding flavors! Making again soon!

